# Family Tree API

![GitHub Workflow Status](https://img.shields.io/github/workflow/status/RianAsmara/ly-tree-be/CI?label=build)

This project is a Genealogy Family Tree API built using Go Fiber with Clean Architecture principles.

## Features

- RESTful API for managing family tree data
- User authentication and authorization
- CRUD operations for family members and relationships
- Swagger documentation
- Docker support for easy deployment

## Tech Stack

- [Go](https://golang.org/) - Programming language
- [Fiber](https://gofiber.io/) - Web framework
- [GORM](https://gorm.io/) - ORM library
- [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/) - Database
- [Swagger](https://swagger.io/) - API documentation
- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/) - Containerization

## Project Structure

The project follows Clean Architecture principles:

- `client`: External service clients
- `configuration`: Application and database configuration
- `controller`: HTTP request handlers
- `docs`: Swagger documentation
- `exception`: Custom error handling
- `repository`: Data access layer
- `service`: Business logic layer

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.16+
- Docker and Docker Compose

### Running the Application

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/RianAsmara/personal-finance-advisor-api.git
   cd family-tree-be
   ```

2. Build and run the application using Docker Compose:

   ```bash
   make run
   ```

3. The API will be available at `http://localhost:9999`

### Running Tests

To run the tests:

```bash
make test
```
